content.description: SDS on high right hand gaston and lower micro crimp gaston for left. Muscle up to gain the starting left hold of Waffles and Wifi
content.location: Low start to Waffles and Wifi

content.description: Start as for Stage Right and traverse left topping out on Latter or start as for Latter, traverse right and top out on (aka exit) Stage Right.
content.protection: A pad for the top out
content.location: The Warm-up center boulder.

content.description: Start with double gastons at head height. Move left to a flake before topping out. Fun sequence.
content.location: A few feet right of Trail Booger.

content.description: Sit start with a side-pull and ledge, climb right, to the key undercling. Toss for the sloper and top out.
content.location: Between Former and Trail Spice at the Warm-up Center.

content.description: SDS matched on a positive block, gain the big slot and climb excellent edges to the top. Great sequence!
content.location: Center route on the Warm-up Center, just right of Former

content.description: Two ways to climb the crack, the easier starts off the block, the other traverses in from the right
content.location: off the left side of the trail before the point

content.description: SDS with a side pull for the left and the large sloping ledge in the right. Climb the arete. Very technical. Body positions are kind of scrunched, may be easier if you’re short.
content.location: This dome-like boulder sits just to the left of the trail and is the first you encounter as you walk to the point.

climbs.name: That Chossy Good for Nothing Traverse

content.description: SDS all the way left on a big ledge and sidepull. Traverse left, topping out just before the outcrop ends. Questionable rock quality.
content.location: The long rock band left of the Trail Roof and above the Trail Booger Boulder.

content.description: Start matched on a rail, climb up the slab using sloping edges.
content.location: Right of The Crawl

content.description: SDS with the two mini triangle pockets. Climb left and up on poor holds topping out as for Stepwise.
content.location: Left of Trail Booger

content.description: Stand start with right hand on the arête at waist heigth and left on a slopey triangular cutout. Techy and progressively easier slab climbing leads to the top out.
content.location: Left of Trail Booger

content.description: SDS with a side pull for the right and left wherever is comfortable, climb positive edges to the top. Detached blocks are off.
content.location: Far right line on the Warm-up center

content.description: Right under the down tree that leans on the boulder. Start with a right handed under cling/crimp and a left hand on a full pad crimp. Not quite a sit start. Reach up with the right to a V shaped crimp. Bring your right foot up and drop the left. Grab a slope-y pinch with the left at hip level to stabilize and then bump it up to a crimp matching the right. Lock off to bring your feet up. Stand up reaching for sloped crimp (crux move). Then either lock off if you are stable enough or a dyno to a sloper top to the right of the crack. Finish with a top out or call it good. I won’t judge.
content.protection: Can be done with 1 pad but I suggest having a spotter
content.location: Follow the path down to the beach and follow it north along the beach to a patch of boulders along the shore. Looking for the boulder that has a dead tree leaning against it. It’s about half way to the point of the cove.

content.description: SDS low on the big flake. Ride tasty side pulls to the top!
content.location: Left of Deliverance

content.description: SDS with a right hand edge and whatever you can find for the left. Slab it out. Questionable rock quality.
content.location: Left of the Altruist

content.description: SDS on a nice in-cut before climbing through more positive ledges to the top. Nice grips, short but sweet.
content.location: Vertical face left of the Trail Booger Boulder

content.description: SDS on the largest in-cut in the center of the face. Climb edges and slots to the top. Watch out for loose blocks as you near the top out.
content.location: The high-angle slab right of the Trail Roof

content.description: SDS matched on a slanting in-cut, climb the arete-like feature of the ramp till you reach the top.
content.location: Beneath the ramp feature, just right of Trail Spice.

content.description: Start with right hand on the arête and left on a small edge. A few delicate moves lead to the top.
content.location: South arête of the freestanding, pyramid shaped block beneath the Trail Roof

content.description: Stand start, layback the arête and top out. All detached blocks and adjacent walls are off.
content.protection: A pad if you can squeeze it
content.location: South arête of the freestanding, pyramid shaped block beneath the Trail Roof.

content.description: Start low on the arête. Some laybacking on poor feet leads to a slopey top out.
content.location: West arête of the freestanding, pyramid shaped block beneath the Trail Roof

content.description: Start Crouched with right hand low on the arête  and left on a small edge. Climb the arête before sneaking left under the roof and topping out. Fun movement with an awkward landing and poor position. All detached blocks and adjacent walls are off.
content.protection: Maybe a pad if you can squeeze it in there
content.location: East arête of the freestanding, pyramid shaped block beneath the Trail Roof.

content.description: SDS on a triangle feature, climb positive in-cuts before reaching the top out.
content.location: Far left line on the Warm-up Center Boulder

content.description: SDS on two side pulls compress positive edges to the top. Rock quality is questionable, landing is sketchy.
content.location: Triangle shaped face left and just uphill of the main face of the Warm-up Center

content.description: An awkward start with two sidepulls leads to mellower climbing and a top out. Adjacent left wall is off
content.location: Left of Serendipitously

content.description: SDS on a matched on a protruding block. Climb similar positive features to the top.
content.location: Just left of Latter.

content.description: SDS matched on an in-cut flake, climb positive ledges before mantling on to the ramp and topping out.
content.location: Beneath and right of the ramp feature. Just right of Ramparts.

content.description: Start crouched with opposed slopers and poor feet. A few heady moves lead to a milder top out.
content.location: Left of Self Service

content.description: Stand start in on the face just left of the roof. Climb the dihedral till you reach the prominent crack. Layback and follow the crack up and around a bulge before topping out. Excellent climb, bad landing. The freestanding block behind you is off!
content.protection: No good place for pads or spotters
content.location: Dihedral on the left side of the Trail Roof boulder.

content.description: SDS on a low rail. Climb up into the right angling sloping ledge before moving left and topping out.
content.location: Right of Rotifer

content.description: Stand start with a left hand pocket and small right hand tooth. Climb the up the slab using sloping ledges and cool pockets.
content.location: Left side of the slabby face just right of the Stage Right.

content.description: SDS as for Daphnia, but upon reaching the right angling sloping rail head right toping out in the slight dihedral.
content.location: Right of Daphnia

content.description: SDS with right hand pinch and left hand gaston. Slopey edges and some high stepping defends the top out.
content.location: Left of Stepwise

content.description: Trail-side bouldering on several outcrops and freestanding blocks. The high density of climbs in the V0 range makes this an ideal warm-up area
